19:37.694 --> 19:44.786
David is grieving the loss of his son, but he's grieving so loud that all the soldiers that come back from the victory, all they can hear is this king wailing

19:45.602 --> 19:47.986
My son, Absalom, my son, my son.

19:48.306 --> 19:54.737
And instead of walking home as victorious, like the underdogs who fought for their king and won, their heads are down.

19:56.139 --> 20:00.947
Like their cowards, like they were scared and they're losing heart.

20:01.427 --> 20:06.956
And Joab sees his king lost in sorrow, lost in emotion.

20:07.778 --> 20:10.121
And he needs to give him a wake up.

20:10.141 --> 20:13.106
He walks in, he's like, David, David, pay attention.

20:14.818 --> 20:22.108
I understand, you're sad, I understand, you lost yourself, but listen, it feels like to all of us that you would rather, all of us were dead in Absalom was alive.

20:22.128 --> 20:23.790
They just risked their lives for you, these men.

20:25.012 --> 20:29.197
And you need to go out there and you need to encourage them because they fought for you.

20:29.498 --> 20:30.579
So snap out of it.

20:31.721 --> 20:34.665
And how many of you know that we need a friend like that some days?

20:36.227 --> 20:44.498
Like, I don't know about you, but maybe in the last couple of weeks, maybe some of you had a good enough friend to walk up to you and say,

20:44.578 --> 20:45.239
Are you okay?

20:46.741 --> 20:47.663
Because you look off.

20:49.145 --> 20:50.006
That thing you posted?

20:51.048 --> 20:53.411
That was off.

20:54.052 --> 20:55.495
That sense of anger you have on your face?

20:57.317 --> 20:58.219
That feels off for you.

20:58.920 --> 21:01.984
That overwhelming sense of sadness you're carrying with you all the time.

21:02.024 --> 21:02.886
It feels off.

21:02.906 --> 21:07.252
Can I help you not get lost in the emotion of this moment or the situation?

21:07.413 --> 21:10.157
And can I remind you of who you are and who you serve?

21:10.217 --> 21:13.682
And sometimes we need a good friend.

21:14.722 --> 21:18.988
to give us a little, to help us get back on track.

21:19.008 --> 21:24.797
And David listens to Joab, and David goes out and honors his men and their sacrifice.

21:25.278 --> 21:27.101
And that's the beautiful thing I love about David.

21:27.521 --> 21:32.509
He's willing to yield his feelings and thoughts to people who might have a different perspective than him.

21:32.950 --> 21:35.974
And in this moment, he leads his people.

21:36.094 --> 21:39.640
Now, David has just won a victory.

21:40.361 --> 21:41.202
Remember, he was,

21:41.410 --> 21:43.613
exiled from his kingdom, the coup happened.

21:43.894 --> 21:48.741
He fought and overwhelmed with a bigger force than him and won, and now he's gonna go back and be king.

21:48.761 --> 21:50.904
But you can't just march back into Jerusalem.

21:50.964 --> 21:55.130
No, he's gotta go through this long process of reconciliation.

21:56.052 --> 21:58.816
And so he's still far away from Jerusalem.

21:59.537 --> 22:05.546
And now watch what happens as he begins the conversation to come back to be the king.

22:06.227 --> 22:11.154
Verse nine, throughout the tribes of Israel, all the people were arguing among themselves, saying,

22:11.682 --> 22:13.744
The king delivered us from the hand of our enemies.

22:14.285 --> 22:16.527
He's the one who rescued us from the land of the Philistines.

22:16.988 --> 22:19.491
But now he's fled the country to escape from Absalom.

22:20.091 --> 22:23.075
And Absalom, who he anointed to rule over us, has died in battle.

22:23.755 --> 22:26.198
So why do you say nothing about bringing the king back?

22:27.600 --> 22:32.145
This is the 10 tribes of Israel, the northern tribes of Israel, David's from the tribe of Judah.

22:32.905 --> 22:38.091
And there's all this talk like, hey, we picked Absalom over David.

22:38.712 --> 22:39.312
How did that happen?

22:39.332 --> 22:40.754
You see they're arguing back and forth.

22:41.058 --> 22:44.642
This whole thing happened because of division within a nation, within people.

22:45.482 --> 22:48.005
Maybe it started kind of harmlessly.

22:48.045 --> 22:49.046
I don't know.

22:49.066 --> 22:52.689
Do you think David's like a good king, like as good as he was?

22:52.710 --> 22:53.851
I think he's lost his touch.

22:53.891 --> 22:54.892
He's lost his edge.

22:56.173 --> 22:57.975
And frankly, Absalom's pretty good looking.

22:58.956 --> 22:59.736
He pretty care his magic.

22:59.756 --> 23:00.938
He made a lot of promises.

23:02.259 --> 23:05.402
So maybe, maybe David's like past his prime.

23:05.422 --> 23:06.503
Maybe we should pick Absalom.

23:06.543 --> 23:09.426
You know, all these divisions start with little conversations like that.

23:09.602 --> 23:11.825
where people say, no, don't quote me on this, but I heard.

23:12.886 --> 23:18.973
And it's really slander and it's really completely destructive to the people of God, but it's sort of the accepted sin.

23:19.033 --> 23:21.516
And now there's all this other conversation.

23:21.536 --> 23:24.620
Well, you know, we rejected David, but now Absalom is dead.

23:24.680 --> 23:26.282
So we probably need to ask David back.

23:26.342 --> 23:27.724
This is the fickleness of people, right?

23:29.146 --> 23:31.348
And so this conversation is going on with Israel.

23:31.388 --> 23:34.832
Now, word comes to David that this whole conversation's happening.

23:34.853 --> 23:36.114
Look at me in verse 11.

23:36.834 --> 23:48.730
Then King David sent this message to Zadok and Abiathar, the priests, asked the elders of Judah, why should you be the last to bring the king back to his palace, since what is being said throughout Israel has reached the king at his quarters?

23:49.591 --> 23:54.858
You were my relatives, my own flesh and blood, so why should you be the last to bring back the king?

23:55.639 --> 23:59.424
And he said to a master, are you not my flesh and blood?

24:00.065 --> 24:06.674
May God deal with me, be it ever so severely, if you're not the commander of my army, for life in the place of Joab.

24:07.426 --> 24:11.131
and he won over the hearts of the men of Judah so that they were of one mind.

24:11.651 --> 24:15.676
And they sent word to the king of return and all your men.

24:17.198 --> 24:17.819
What's happening?

24:17.839 --> 24:19.821
You have a nation divided.

24:20.262 --> 24:22.044
You have a civil war that's just occurred.

24:22.925 --> 24:26.089
And now the 10 tribes that were against David said, let's bring him back.

24:26.910 --> 24:29.954
But David's like, first of all, my own tribe, Judah has to ask me to come back.

24:29.974 --> 24:32.377
He's only going to come back if he's invited to come back.

24:32.397 --> 24:33.618
He's not going to storm back in.

24:34.720 --> 24:36.562
David's holding his kingdom very loosely.

24:37.730 --> 24:40.513
And so he appeals to his own people, Judah.

24:40.914 --> 24:42.476
Am I not your flesh and blood?

24:42.516 --> 24:44.999
Jerusalem's the capital city of this area.

24:45.980 --> 24:50.185
And wasn't I the one who led you and he appeals to their anxieties?

24:50.225 --> 24:53.829
Don't be the last tribe to invite me back, but be the first tribe.

24:54.050 --> 24:55.752
And everyone gets together like, you know what?

24:55.792 --> 24:56.172
You're right.

24:56.192 --> 24:58.755
Well, I don't know why we picked Absalom over David anyway.

24:58.775 --> 25:00.357
And we want to be the ones that invite him back.

25:00.377 --> 25:04.142
And so he gets invited back into Jerusalem.

25:04.222 --> 25:07.506
And so we're going to watch David make this

25:08.034 --> 25:10.237
Long walk home.

25:10.257 --> 25:10.938
This long road.

25:11.819 --> 25:15.264
Remember, it was just a few weeks early, he was walking out of the city.

25:16.125 --> 25:17.127
And that was he walking out of the city.

25:17.167 --> 25:19.630
People were cursing at him and throwing stones and rocks at him.

25:19.670 --> 25:22.494
And people were slandering him and manipulating him.

25:22.515 --> 25:23.396
And now he's going to turn around.

25:23.416 --> 25:23.997
He's going to walk back.

25:24.157 --> 25:26.961
And he's going to walk back past all those same characters.

25:28.082 --> 25:31.627
So the first person he meets on the way back is a man named Shimeon.

25:32.469 --> 25:36.274
He was the guy that was throwing rocks and dirt and cursing to David on the way out.

25:37.410 --> 25:43.036
And he falls down right in front of David on his face and he begs for his life.

25:43.096 --> 25:45.519
Have mercy on me, I sin, I shouldn't have said it.

25:46.680 --> 25:49.503
And Abishai, he's right hand guy said, can I cut off his head?

25:50.664 --> 25:51.605
That's what he said on the way out.

25:51.645 --> 25:52.526
Can I cut off his guy's head?

25:52.927 --> 25:54.348
Same thing, Abishai is very consistent.

25:54.368 --> 25:54.989
Let me cut off his head.

25:57.211 --> 26:01.156
And David wouldn't have been wrong to say, yeah, it's time now.

26:01.997 --> 26:06.962
Now that I'm one, now that I have total control, I can use this moment

26:07.106 --> 26:10.773
vindicate myself, cut off his head, make an example of him.

26:11.495 --> 26:12.317
But you know what David says?

26:13.639 --> 26:14.621
No one's going to die today.

26:15.964 --> 26:18.669
You see, he's not interested in vengeance.

26:18.770 --> 26:24.882
He's interested in this very fragile nation being reunited back together again, and he knows that his

26:25.026 --> 26:26.407
sin and the rebellion.

26:26.427 --> 26:32.614
And the exile has created so much division within the nation, within the tribes, that he's going to have to wisely navigate.

26:32.714 --> 26:34.396
So he says, Shimea is not going to die.

26:34.416 --> 26:44.847
Then he takes a few more steps and he sees this guy, Ziba, who manipulated David and a man named Mephibosheth, who was a steward of Ziba, or was Ziba was his steward.

26:45.828 --> 26:51.474
And Ziba on the way out lied and said, Mephibosheth has sold you out, but the reality is, Mephibosheth comes and he's got

26:51.650 --> 26:54.935
His nails haven't been trimmed, his beard hasn't been shaved, he hasn't changed his clothes.

26:55.276 --> 26:55.917
He's been mourning.

26:55.937 --> 26:58.081
He said, I've been mourning every day since you've been gone.

26:58.121 --> 27:02.087
I did not betray you, but he, my servant betrayed me and you gave him all my property.

27:02.107 --> 27:03.089
And I don't even need it back.

27:03.109 --> 27:06.635
I just need you to know I've never been disloyal to you.

27:08.237 --> 27:14.107
And David has a chance in this moment for perfect justice to say, is he who you lied?

27:14.127 --> 27:18.514
So all the stuff belongs to him and I'm throwing you in jail, but he does what is pragmatic.

27:20.322 --> 27:22.205
He says, I'm gonna split it 50-50.

27:23.326 --> 27:28.414
Because again, he needs Ziba and Saul's family to be supportive, to bring the kingdom back together.

27:28.434 --> 27:36.086
And he says to him, Massa, the general for Absalom who led the rebellion, I'm gonna make you the general of our army over Joab.

27:36.106 --> 27:37.768
And you're like, why is he doing this?

27:39.090 --> 27:43.116
Because he wants every soldier to know that was a part of the rebellion, part of the coup.

27:43.737 --> 27:46.361
I'm not gonna kill anyone.

27:46.381 --> 27:47.082
Everything's forgiven.

27:48.124 --> 27:49.746
And this type of leadership,

27:50.370 --> 28:07.787
Reminds me of one of America's greatest presidents, a man named Abraham Lincoln, who after the Civil War, when Union leaders were saying, we need to execute some of these generals, we need to kill some of these soldiers, we need to imprison people, and Abraham Lincoln says, no one else is gonna die.

28:08.948 --> 28:19.218
We had brothers fighting against brothers, and a lot of blood was shed, but we need to bring the nation back together again, because a house divided against itself cannot stand.

28:20.002 --> 28:21.344
Aren't you grateful for leaders like that?

28:21.384 --> 28:26.570
And David demonstrates this in this moment.

28:26.590 --> 28:28.453
Now, where did Abraham Lincoln get that line?

28:28.493 --> 28:30.315
A house divided against itself cannot stand.

28:31.496 --> 28:32.417
He got it from Jesus.

28:33.959 --> 28:44.012
And Jesus was using that sentence to describe the fact that Satan's own army, his demonic forces, the way the evil works in the world is not divided against itself.

28:44.252 --> 28:48.978
They're unified to kill and steal and destroy

28:49.538 --> 28:50.699
against God's people.

28:51.280 --> 28:56.406
And Jesus is making a powerful point if Satan's own kingdom is not divided, why should God's house be divided?

28:57.328 --> 29:02.694
Why would we allow an enemy to be unified against us and us to be divided against ourselves?

29:02.734 --> 29:07.420
And David shows us, again, this very powerful lesson.

29:07.440 --> 29:12.466
The last thing that we see in this chapter is David meets a guy named Barzilla.

29:13.218 --> 29:17.044
This is the man who is 80 years old who provided all this provision for David and his army.

29:17.064 --> 29:19.728
And he says to Brazil, I want you to come back to Jerusalem, sit at my table.

29:20.189 --> 29:21.891
I'll feed you for the rest of my life.

29:21.911 --> 29:23.955
You'll be honored among my leaders.

29:24.015 --> 29:25.377
And he's like, I'm an old man.

29:25.557 --> 29:28.401
I didn't do this for reward, but you can take my son.

29:28.461 --> 29:29.403
He can sit at your table.

29:29.443 --> 29:39.899
And you watch this beautiful process of David honoring his friends and not punishing his enemies as he brings unity back to the people of God.

29:41.081 --> 29:41.842
And so this

29:42.882 --> 29:45.165
3,000 year old story has some relevance to us today.

29:45.185 --> 29:47.108
I want to talk about just three of these ideas.

29:48.149 --> 29:50.052
Here's the first one.

29:50.072 --> 29:51.173
It's never too late to come home.

29:52.775 --> 30:04.571
No matter how far away you wandered, no matter how long you've been there in your doubt, in your sin, in your shame, in your addiction, in your brokenness, in your pride, in your numbness, whatever it is, there's always a way back.

30:06.214 --> 30:12.402
And the way back is not to rewind and make what you said and did go away because life does not have a rewind

30:12.546 --> 30:17.494
remote, it's just to go through the process and know you are never too far.

30:17.554 --> 30:25.067
So David would later write this Psalm about how we walk through difficult circumstances.

30:25.127 --> 30:32.139
He would write in Psalm 34, his anger, that's God's anger, lasts only a moment, but his favor lasts a lifetime.

30:33.341 --> 30:38.770
Weeping may stay for the night, but rejoicing comes in the morning.

30:39.970 --> 30:41.112
Aren't you grateful for that?

30:41.132 --> 30:43.795
That God's anger is just for a moment.

30:45.297 --> 30:48.061
The consequence for our sin, just for a moment.

30:48.101 --> 30:49.843
His rebuke, just for a moment.

30:50.003 --> 30:52.647
He hurts us to heal us, to draw us back.

30:53.147 --> 30:57.673
But when we go to sleep in tears and anger, and we wake up in the morning, it's like resurrection.

30:57.734 --> 31:00.717
God can make all things new.

31:00.758 --> 31:01.719
He's done it in my life.

31:01.759 --> 31:02.840
I know he's done it in your life.

31:03.201 --> 31:05.484
And this is the beautiful thing about the nature of God.

31:06.505 --> 31:07.186
When we sin.

31:08.258 --> 31:13.667
There are consequences, even when forgiveness comes, but those consequences don't last forever.

31:14.528 --> 31:16.531
Here's how Moses would write about the faithfulness of God.

31:16.832 --> 31:20.838
Lord, through all the generations, you have been our home.

31:22.120 --> 31:23.602
Think about that powerful concept.

31:24.484 --> 31:33.458
Moses and David are both like, no matter what happens in life, highest, highest, lowest, lowest wins and losses, no matter what happens in your life, God is always home for you.

31:34.466 --> 31:43.497
I don't know if anyone here has teenagers or 20 something, but if you have kids that are driving and kids that stay out late, one of the ways is a parent, you want to always let your kids know their welcome is to keep the light on.

31:45.800 --> 31:49.785
And always say no matter what time you come, there's always food at the table.

31:49.806 --> 31:50.727
You're always welcome at the table.

31:51.768 --> 31:52.369
God's like that.

31:53.530 --> 31:54.331
And you wander away.

31:54.351 --> 31:54.892
You do your own thing.

31:54.912 --> 32:02.021
He always leaves the light on and there's always a seat at the table because there's something about coming home, the sense of identity.

32:02.081 --> 32:02.802
I belong here.

32:03.362 --> 32:04.124
The sense of purpose.

32:04.144 --> 32:04.865
This is my father.

32:04.885 --> 32:05.546
These are my people.

32:05.586 --> 32:06.388
This is my family.

32:06.608 --> 32:08.933
And this is what God has called in the Bible.

32:08.973 --> 32:11.158
He has called the father and he invites us to his table.

32:11.198 --> 32:15.306
And so it's never too late to come home.

32:15.346 --> 32:18.372
Second idea, coming home requires repairing relationships.

32:19.374 --> 32:25.426
David has a lot to repair, even though he's been this far away.

32:26.018 --> 32:29.804
And even though he walks back and starts to restore the nation, there's a lot, there's a mess.

32:29.824 --> 32:36.835
I don't know if you've ever experienced a break-in where you come into your house and stuff is everywhere and you're trying to figure out what's gone, what's missing, what's broken, how do I put it back together?

32:36.915 --> 32:40.280
Maybe it was a storm or a flood, all the stuff is everywhere.

32:40.300 --> 32:41.081
You're like, this is a mess.

32:41.682 --> 32:45.167
Yeah, and David's gonna walk back into Jerusalem and it's an absolute mess.

32:46.189 --> 32:54.642
There's still division, there's a rebellion that's gonna come in the next chapter as people like, I don't want him to be king and he already messed up and I think this and I think that and all that stuff is going on.

32:54.786 --> 32:58.491
In this moment, he's gonna have to have difficult conversations with Joab, his general.

32:59.753 --> 33:02.377
He has to have a difficult conversation with Ziba and Shimea.

33:02.397 --> 33:08.125
He's gonna have to have difficult conversations with the nation of Judah and the nations of the tribes of Israel.

33:08.145 --> 33:18.419
And there's gonna be the moments where he confronts, where he apologizes, moments where he asks for forgiveness and extends forgiveness, moments of restoration.

33:18.680 --> 33:23.026
This is gonna be difficult and deep and very hard work.

33:24.258 --> 33:30.744
It's one thing to come home and say, God's forgiven me, and I'm so free, but all the other relationships of your life are gonna need this repair.

33:31.885 --> 33:34.928
And Jesus would say this about this difficult work of peacemaking.

33:36.150 --> 33:41.575
Blessed are the peacemakers, for they will be called the children of God.

33:43.497 --> 33:46.059
You know, it's so much easier to sweep it under the rug.

33:47.521 --> 33:49.423
It's so much easier to pretend like it was never an issue.

33:49.623 --> 33:51.224
All's forgiven, let's forget, let's move on.

33:51.245 --> 33:52.786
No, no, no, no, no, no, no, no.

33:53.122 --> 34:01.094
We see David going through each one of these conversations with people trying to bring repair and peace and well, this week has been one of those challenges.

34:01.134 --> 34:22.386
Maybe you found yourself between someone on your family over here and someone in your family here and you're in the middle and you're trying to get them not to hate each other or judge each other or cancel each other and you're like, guys, and then you get attacked from both sides and Jesus would say to you, if you're that peacemaker, blessed are you if you're making peace in the family of God because you will be called the son or daughter of God in that process.

34:23.330 --> 34:25.032
Can I talk to you just for a moment as your pastor?

34:26.795 --> 34:43.018
I'm gonna say that we've seen a lot in these last 10 days and it's sad and can make you angry and can be heartbreaking, but one of the saddest things for me is watching the way that Christians have treated other Christians.

34:44.440 --> 34:51.410
On social media, in their own small groups and their own families, I've had so many conversations with people like I can't talk to my own family

34:51.938 --> 35:04.479
I can't talk to this person in my group and he said this and she said that and this person has judged me or said this and people are so free to say what they think about people without talking to people.

35:05.922 --> 35:15.698
I want to say this, don't be the person who talks about people without talking to them first because this is what Satan loves to do.

35:16.450 --> 35:19.874
We talked last week about this quiet revival that's stirring across this nation.

35:20.034 --> 35:21.476
People are hungry for hope.

35:21.496 --> 35:22.557
They're looking for God.

35:23.878 --> 35:26.762
And if you were saying, how would you stop it?

35:28.123 --> 35:28.363
I know.

35:28.384 --> 35:30.746
I get Christians to fight among themselves.

35:31.487 --> 35:33.369
I get them to say hateful things to each other online.

35:33.409 --> 35:35.011
I get them to cancel each other and not talk.

35:35.311 --> 35:39.897
And then people would look on and go, if that's Christianity, no, thank you.

35:40.077 --> 35:44.722
I'm looking for something that's right and true.

35:45.858 --> 35:49.222
And so it's not enough just to say, it's the truth, and I said it.

35:51.104 --> 36:13.490
Now, if you didn't say it like Jesus said it, and you're a follower of Jesus, then you need to repent and say, God, I've actually been divisive this week in the words, in the tone, in the rhetoric, and I've judged hundreds, thousands, millions of people who see things this way, or this way, and God, I want to repent for that because Jesus

36:14.594 --> 36:18.740
your prayers that we might be once, so that the world will know that you sent me.

36:20.042 --> 36:21.524
We wanna answer the prayer of Jesus.

36:21.544 --> 36:23.908
We wanna speak the truth in love.

36:24.449 --> 36:26.272
Kindness is not softness.

36:27.614 --> 36:29.076
Kindness is Christ's likeness.

36:30.157 --> 36:38.009
And so how do we speak into the mess, into the darkness with the power and conviction of who Jesus is and what he's done?

36:38.450 --> 36:41.054
Because he is our savior.

36:41.074 --> 36:41.655
Amen church?

36:42.376 --> 36:43.077
This is who he is.

36:43.197 --> 36:43.858
And listen.

36:45.890 --> 36:48.553
He's given us this mission.

36:48.994 --> 36:51.577
He has committed to us the message of reconciliation.

36:52.277 --> 36:55.922
What he did between us and God, removing the sin, the divide.

36:56.282 --> 36:58.184
Now he invites us to do with other people.

36:59.045 --> 37:00.287
These divides between people.

37:00.427 --> 37:02.109
And here's the challenge with that.

37:02.269 --> 37:03.450
Some people are hard to love.

37:03.570 --> 37:05.993
If you have someone in your life who's hard to love, raise your hand.

37:07.495 --> 37:08.416
If they're next, you don't look at them.

37:08.436 --> 37:09.057
Just look straight ahead.

37:09.798 --> 37:13.522
Listen, people are hard to love.

37:13.602 --> 37:16.226
And here's what Jesus said about the last day.

37:16.266 --> 37:18.890
He says, evil is gonna increase more and more and more.

37:18.930 --> 37:20.251
It's gonna increase so much.

37:20.472 --> 37:24.898
Listen to this, that the love of most people's hearts will grow cold.

